15|76|And verily, they were right on the highroad.
15|77|Surely, there is indeed a sign in that for the believers.
15|78|And the Dwellers of Al-Aykah, were also wrongdoers.
15|79|So, We took vengeance on them. They are both on an open route, plain to see.
15|80|And verily, the Dwellers of Al-Hijr denied the Messengers.
15|81|And We gave them Our signs, but they were averse to them.
15|82|And they used to hew out dwellings from the mountains, (feeling) secure.
15|83|But the Sayhah (torment - awful cry) overtook them in the early morning.
