29|1|Alif Lam Mim.
29|2|Do people think that they will be left alone because they say: "We believe," and will not be tested.
29|3|And We indeed tested those who were before them so that Allah will indeed know those who are true, and He will know those who are liars.
29|4|Or think those who do evil deeds that they can outstrip Us Evil is that which they judge!
29|5|Whoever hopes in meeting with Allah, then Allah's term is surely coming, and He is the All-Hearer, the All-Knower.
29|6|And whosoever strives, he strives only for himself. Verily, Allah stands not in need of any of the creatures.
29|7|Those who believe, and do righteous good deeds, surely, We shall expiate from them their evil deeds and We shall indeed reward them according to the best of that which they used to do.
29|8|And We have enjoined on man to be dutiful to his parents; but if they strive to make you associate with Me, which you have no knowledge of, then obey them not. Unto Me is your return and I shall tell you what you used to do.
29|9|And for those who believe and do righteous deeds, surely, We shall admit them among the righteous.
29|10|Of mankind are some who say: "We believe in Allah." But if they are made to suffer for Allah, they consider the trial of mankind as Allah's punishment; and if victory comes from your Lord, they will say: "Verily, we were with you." Is not Allah Best Aware of what is in the breasts of the creatures
29|11|And indeed Allah knows those who believe, and verily, He knows the hypocrites.
29|12|And those who disbelieve say to those who believe: "Follow our way and let us bear your sins." Never will they bear anything of their sins. Surely, they are liars.
